  "text": "In a placebo-controlled, randomised, double-blind, parallel-group, fixed-dose study in which placebo, ESC 5, 10, or 20mg/day or paroxetine 20mg/day was administered for 24 weeks that was conducted in countries outside of Japan in SAD [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , the change from treatment initiation in the LSAS total score at week 12 (LOCF, mean) was -29.5 in placebo, -38.7 in ESC 5mg, -34.6 in ESC 10mg, -39.8 in ESC 20mg, and -39.3 in paroxetine. There were no major differences between the studies conducted in Japan and the studies conducted outside Japan in the differences between placebo and either ESC 10mg or ESC 20mg in the change in the LSAS total score at week 12.",
